[This article seems misleading. There is no direct evidence of global warming being the cause of the problem with the sugar cane workers. There are many areas of the world that are hot and people work. However, chronic dehydration is a problem. Lack of electrolyte replacement may also be a problem.

What would be more helpful is to rehydrate these workers, and provide necessary electrolytes and learn if the problem resolves. This study seems very incomplete and is trying to make a case for global warming, not solving a problem in a working environment. - Mod.TG

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3704198,23.]
